observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:

1. Instruct the Inventory Committee to:

a. Prepare and submit a complete Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) to the Audit Team. Henceforth, submit the RCPPE not later than January 31 of each year;

b. Implement the one-time cleansing of PPE and conduct the Physical count pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006;

2. Require the Property Custodian- Designate to:

a. Properly fill out and prepare property cards for each type of PPE;

b. Promptly record and update property cards for any receipt and disposition of PPE, and reconcile with the PPE ledger cards and RCPPE;

c. Prepare the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property for all PPEs found unserviceable; and

3. Require the Municipal Accountant Designate to exert earnest effort in the preparation and maintenance of PPE ledger cards and reconcile with the property cards and RCPPE.

