observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the OIC-Supply officer to:

a. Use the required format of a sequentially numbered Driver’s Trip Ticket duly approved by the Agency Head or the authorized representative with complete information being filled out for all travels undertaken;

b. Reconcile every month the Driver’s Trip Ticket with the Monthly Fuel Consumption Report and Summary of Monthly Report of Official Travels as mandated under COA Circular No. 77-61 to determine whether the said fuel usage is valid and used appropriately; 

c. Utilize the prescribed form such as the Requisition and Issue Voucher, Summary of Requisition and Issue Voucher and Daily Gas issue record as a tool in the monitoring of the receipt and issuance of the fuel;

d. Enforce the “No Properly filled-up Driver’s Trip Ticket, No Trip Policy”,

e. As to the distance travelled, to determine the accurate consumption of fuel:

- All vehicles with functional odometer should record the kilometer reading before and after the trip

- All vehicles with non-functional/defective odometer should indicate the approximate distance traveled including the number of trips undertaken during the day. Immediate repair of the odometer should be considered.

f. Submit to the Audit team the list of vehicles which consumed the 3,850.20 liters of fuel, oil, and lubricants, Approved Driver's Trip Tickets, the Monthly Report of Official travels and Monthly Report of Official Travel.

